3. What is the difference between Declarative and Scripted Pipeline?

Declarative Pipeline is a more user-friendly and structured way to define pipelines,
 while Scripted Pipeline offers more flexibility and control over the pipeline logic.

syntax: 
          Declarative Pipeline:


          pipeline {
              agent any
              stages {
                  stage('Build') {
                      steps {
                          // build steps
                      }
                  }
                  stage('Test') {
                      steps {
                          // test steps
                      }
                  }
                  stage('Deploy') {
                      steps {
                          // deploy steps
                      }
                  }
              }
          }

          Scripted Pipeline:

          node {
              stage('Build') {
                  // build steps
              }
              stage('Test') {
                  // test steps
              }
              stage('Deploy') {
                  // deploy steps
              }
          }
