5. How do you force Jenkins to run a job on a specific node?

  You can use the label parameter in the agent directive. 
For example, if you want to run a job on a node labeled "linux", you can specify it like this:

              pipeline {
                  agent { label 'linux' }
                  stages {
                      stage('Build') {
                          steps {
                              // build steps
                          }
                      }
                  }
              }

