6. How do you run specific stages in a pipeline?

You can use the when directive to conditionally run specific stages in a pipeline.
For example, if you want to run a stage only when the branch is "main", you can specify it like this:

              pipeline {
                  agent any
                  stages {
                      stage('Build') {
                          steps {
                              // build steps
                          }
                      }
                      stage('Test') {
                          when {
                              branch 'main'
                          }
                          steps {
                              // test steps
                          }
                      }
                  }
              }

