9. How do you achieve High Availability in Jenkins?

To achieve High Availability in Jenkins, you can set up a Jenkins master-slave architecture with multiple Jenkins masters and slaves.
This can be done using tools like Jenkins Operations Center or by manually configuring multiple Jenkins instances with shared storage and load balancing.
Load balancers can be used to distribute traffic between the Jenkins masters, and shared storage can be used to ensure that all Jenkins instances have access to the same build artifacts and configurations.


