16. How do you pass parameters to a Jenkins job?

To pass parameters to a Jenkins job, you can use the "This project is parameterized" option in the job configuration.
This allows you to define parameters that can be passed to the job when it is triggered.
For example, you can define a string parameter called "ENVIRONMENT" that allows you to specify

the environment (e.g., dev, qa, prod) to which the job should deploy.
When you trigger the job, you can provide a value for the "ENVIRONMENT" parameter, and the job can use that value in its build steps to determine which environment to deploy to. You can also define other types of parameters such as boolean parameters, choice parameters, or file parameters based on your requirements. 

in pipeline, you can define parameters using the parameters directive. For example:

              pipeline {
                  agent any
                  parameters {
                      string(name: 'ENVIRONMENT', defaultValue: 'dev', description: 'Environment to deploy to')
                  }
                  stages {
                      stage('Deploy') {
                          steps {
                              echo "Deploying to ${params.ENVIRONMENT} environment"
                              // deployment steps based on the ENVIRONMENT parameter
                          }
                      }
                  }
              }

