19. How do you create dependencies between Jenkins jobs?

You can create dependencies between Jenkins jobs using the "Build other projects" option in the job configuration. This allows you to specify that one job should be triggered after another job completes successfully. For example, if you have a build job and a test job, 
you can configure the test job to be triggered automatically after the build job finishes successfully. You can also use plugins like "Parameterized Trigger plugin" to pass parameters from one job to another when creating dependencies between jobs.

