35. What are different types of build triggers in Jenkins?

- SCM Polling: Jenkins periodically checks the source code repository for changes and triggers a build if any changes are detected.
- Webhooks: Jenkins can be triggered by webhooks from version control systems (e.g., GitHub, GitLab) when specific events occur (e.g., code commit, pull request).
- Scheduled Builds: Jenkins can be configured to run builds at specific times using a cron-like syntax
- Manual Trigger: Users can manually trigger a build from the Jenkins UI.
- Upstream/Downstream Trigger: Jenkins can trigger a build of one job after another job completes successfully using the "Build other projects" option in the job configuration.
- Remote Trigger: Jenkins can be triggered remotely using the Jenkins API or command-line interface.


